INSTALL (Ubuntu)
================

First, activate the Universe repositories in the Ubuntu software center.
Then install the following package:

libatlas-base-dev

Make ChemBrows executable, if it is not already:

cd ChemBrows_a_version_number/
sudo chmod +x gui
sudo chmod ChemBrows_a_version_number/gui

Where a_version_number is the version number of the archive you downloaded. 

To start ChemBrows, run in a terminal:

./gui

It should run out of the box (tested on Ubuntu 15.10 and Manjaro Linux).


If you encounter some problems with SSL, run the following commands:

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:fkrull/deadsnakes
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python3.5
cp /usr/lib/python3.5/lib-dynload/_ssl.cpython-35m-x86_64-linux-gnu.so ChemBrows_a_version_number/ChemBrows_a_version_number/

Where a_version_number is the version number of the ChemBrows' archive you downloaded.
Don't worry, these commands will not mess with your current version of Python.

Enjoy !
